10.3 Visits referred to in paragraphs 1 and 2 above require all visitors to have suitable security clearance and a need to know.

10.4 All visit requests shall include the following information:

a) The visitor's first name and surname, the date and place of birth, the nationality and the number of the passport or of the identity card;

b) The job and position of the visitor, the name of the establishment or the institution that employs him / her;

c) The security clearance level of the visitor, authenticated by a security certificate to he provided by the NSCA or CSA of the requesting Party;

d) The proposed date of the visit and the planned duration;

e) The purpose of the visit and all necessary information specifying the subjects to be dealt with that entail Classified Information and their levels of classification;

f) The names of establishments, facilities and premises concerned by the visits;

g) The first names and surnames of the individuals who are to welcome the visitor;

h) The date, signature and official stamp of the NSCA or CSA of the requesting

Party.

10.5 Each Party may request authorization for a visit for a maximum period of twelve (12) months. This authorization can be extended provided that the request is made at least three (3) months prior to its expiry.

10.6 All visitors shall comply with the security, visa and immigration regulations and instructions of the Host Party.

10.7 The Parties may draw up a list of staff authorized to carry out several visits in connection with any project, programme or specific contract in accordance with the standard terms agreed by the NSCA or CSAs of the Parties. At first, said lists shall be valid for a period of twelve (12) months; by agreement between the NSCA or CSAs of the Parties, said period of validity may be extended for other periods that shall not exceed twelve (12) months in all.

